Seoul Bike Sharing Demand

Source: R/bikes.R
bikes.Rd

Seoul Bike Sharing Demand

bikes

Format

A data frame with 8760 rows and 14 variables:

Date

mm/dd/yyyy.

Rented

count of bikes rented at each hour.

Hour

hour of he day.

Temp

temperature in Celsius.

Humidity

humidity in percent.

Wind

wind speed in meters/sec.

Visibility

visibility at 10 meters.

Dew

dew point temperature in celcius.

Solar

solar radiation in Mj/m2.

Rainfall

rainfall in millimeters.

Snowfall

snowfall in centimeters.

Seasons

"Winter", "Spring", "Summer", "Autumn".

Holiday

"Holiday", "No Holiday".

Functioning_Day

Does the rental bike system operate on that day?"Yes", "No" .

Source

Dua, D. and Graff, C. (2019). UCI Machine Learning Repository [http://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml]. Irvine, CA: University of California, School of Information and Computer Science. Seoul Bike Sharing Demand Data Set

Details

The dataset contains the number of public bikes rented at each hour from the Seoul Bike Sharing System with the corresponding Weather and holiday information. Date is recorded as a character variable. It is a good dataset for feature engineering with dates.
